PHASE 6 — MATCH DAY FLOW (ADMIN)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Step 13 — Before match day

  Admin panel → Current Match tab
  Fill in Match Label (e.g. "MI vs CSK — Match 14") and Team 1 / Team 2
  Click "+ Create New Match"
  Click "Find IPL Matches" → select today's match from the list
    → liveMatchId auto-fills, player pool (~51 players) loads
  Share the league URL with your group — they can now pick their teams

Step 14 — After the toss (~30 min before first ball)

  Toggle the "Auto every" dropdown to your preferred interval (e.g. 30 sec)
  and click the "OFF ⏸" button next to it to switch it to "ON 🟢". 
  This will auto-poll for Playing XI updates and match status.
    → If successful, you'll get a "✅ Playing XI auto-detected!" toast.
    → Auto-refresh will continue to update stats once the match starts.

  Alternative: Click "TOSS DONE — FETCH XI"
    → App polls CricAPI every 20 seconds, up to 20 attempts (~7 min)
    → You'll get a "✅ Playing XI confirmed for both teams!" toast if successful
    → No further action needed once confirmed

  If CricAPI doesn't return XI data (API lag between toss and first ball):
    → Expand the "📋 XI not loading from API? Paste manually ▾" panel
       (visible below the FETCH XI button when XI is not yet confirmed)
    → Copy the Playing XI from WhatsApp, Cricbuzz, Tribune India, or any source
    → Paste both teams' names into the textarea (comma or newline separated)
    → For impact substitutes, prefix their line with "Impact:" e.g.:
         Impact: Marcus Stoinis, Xavier Bartlett
    → Click "Mark Playing XI"
    → App fuzzy-matches names against the player pool and sets XI ready

Step 15 — First ball

  Click "START MATCH"
    → All member picks are locked (no more edits)
    → Leaderboard reveals simultaneously for everyone
    → Live stats poller starts (auto-updates every ~5 minutes)

  Keep your admin browser tab open during the match — the poller only
  runs while the tab is active.

Step 16 — During the match

  Points update live for everyone automatically
  After each innings, check the Player Stats tab for any missing
  catches, stumpings, or run-outs — fix them manually if needed

Step 17 — After the match

  Poller fires one final fetch 60 seconds after CricAPI signals match over
    → This grace poll captures any last-over stats that lagged behind
  You'll see: "🏁 Final stats saved. Click 'Finalize & Save' when ready."
  Fix any remaining fielding stats
  Click "✅ Finalize & Save to Season" → confirm
    → Points locked into the season leaderboard permanently


