TROUBLESHOOTING
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Player images not showing up
  → Go to Admin tab → Current Match.
  → Click the 🔄 button next to "Find IPL Matches". 
  → This will look up official IDs and populate headshots for all players.
  → Refresh the page after the sync completes.

"API Connection Failed" or "Failed to Fetch"
  → 1. Ensure you are running from http://localhost or Netlify (not file://).
  → 2. Ensure your API Key is saved in Admin → Current Match.
  → 3. The app includes an automatic proxy fallback to bypass network resets. 
     If it still fails, try switching to a mobile hotspot.

App stuck on Loading screen
  → Most likely a JavaScript error on boot. Hard-refresh (Ctrl+Shift+R /
    Cmd+Shift+R). If it persists, check the browser console for errors.

"Firebase Not Configured" screen
  → Re-open the HTML file, verify all REPLACE_* values were replaced,
    re-save, re-upload to Netlify.

Firestore permission denied error
  → Firebase Console → Firestore → Rules → confirm Step 4 was done
    and "Publish" was clicked.

Playing XI not loading after toss
  → Click "TOSS DONE — FETCH XI" — the watcher polls for ~7 minutes.
    If it times out, use the "📋 XI not loading from API?" panel that
    appears below the button. Copy the XI from anywhere (WhatsApp,
    Cricbuzz, Tribune India) and paste it in. The app fuzzy-matches
    names and marks XI ready automatically.

Players not loading from "Find IPL Matches"
  → Check the API key is saved (Admin → Current Match → API Key).
    Try again after a minute — CricAPI occasionally has brief delays.

Final-over stats not showing after match ends
  → The poller automatically fires one final fetch 60 seconds after
    CricAPI reports the match as over — this captures last-over data.
    Wait for the "Final stats saved" toast before clicking Finalize.
    If stats are still missing, correct them manually in the Player
    Stats grid before finalizing.

Someone forgot their PIN
  → They can re-register with the same join link using the same name
    and a new PIN — it overwrites the old one.

Auto-refresh stops during match
  → Poller only runs while the admin browser tab is open and active.
    Keep your screen on during the match.

Stats look wrong after auto-fetch
  → Manually correct them in the Player Stats grid — your edits
    override the API data.

Booster not saving
  → If your team is already locked in, the booster saves automatically
    on apply/remove. If team is not yet locked, booster is staged locally
    and saves when you click "Lock In My Team".


